d87bd81e13-10-02 d87bd81eSweat Equity Blodgett Peak FAd87bd81e d87bd81e15 months since Blodgett closed for the fire. My knees and excitement have rekindled and the work begins again. This was the last problem I visited (only 6 days before the fire) and it felt good to take care of it. It is in the burn area but like all the rock so far, it is unscathed. Stand start on the face to the right of Hemogoblin with both hands matched in the odd small hole. Time to crush other unfinished projects. ***d87bd81e

d797b4fb15-10-20 d797b4fbEliminati Ute valley  d797b4fb d797b4fbAn eliminate but worth mentioning. On the overhanging arte feature, start at the large flake and stay under the arte the whole time.
